data.title: Andrew II “the Jerosolimitan” of Hungary ...
data.meta_description: Andrew II the Jerosolimitan was King of Hungary  and Croatia. Andrew was the second son of King Béla III and his first wife, Agnes of Antioch. As younger son, Andrew had no hope to inherite the Kingdom of Hungary from his father who wanted to ensure the inheritance of his elder son, Emeric and had him crowned already...
